cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

This paper is about natural language processing and machine learning models, which suggests it belongs to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) category. The use of neural networks also suggests it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) categories. The mention of weighted finite-state automata (WFSAs) suggests it could also belong to the cs.SD (Sound) category, which includes speech recognition and synthesis. Finally, the use of recurrent and convolutional neural networks suggests it could also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category.
